    <string name="about_changelog_title">Changelog</string>
    <string name="about_changelog_text"></string>
    <string name="welcome_tile_title">Welcome to KlippShell! 👋</string>
    <string name="welcome_tile_msg">Glad you\'re here! To help you get the most out of your printer monitoring, here is a brief overview of KlippShell\'s core features and the specific characteristics of some TV devices. KlippShell is designed to run on smartphones, tablets, or user-friendly on Android TV.\n\n1️⃣ FIRST STEPS\nAdd your first 3D printer below. Currently, almost all models on the market are included. If you want to use another Klipper-based printer, you can select \"Custom Model\".\nNote: Depending on the printer model and network configuration, you may need to adjust your ports and camera access manually to ensure flawless monitoring. However, the automatic network scan should handle most configurations automatically.\n⚠️ If you don\'t get a live image of the printer, please visit https://github.com/DnG-Crafts/K2-Camera and install the FIX. This unfortunately requires root rights on the printer!\n💡 Tip: A long press on one of your saved printers in the main menu opens the options to change the default view between Live-Stream Monitoring and Klipper OS, or to delete this printer.\n\n2️⃣ SMART LIVE CONTROL\nIn video stream mode, you control everything via three main lower buttons:\n• Left button: Opens the menu for On-Screen Display (OSD), video zoom, PiP, enclosure lighting, screensaver, and aspect ratio.\n• Middle button: Seamlessly switches between Klipper OS (Dashboard) and the pure camera live stream.\n• Right button: Brings you safely back to the main menu at any time.\n\n3️⃣ DIRECT START MODE\nOnce you have successfully configured a printer, you can select Direct Start Mode in the settings. This allows you to start directly in the live stream view upon app launch.\n\n4️⃣ THE COMPANION MODE\nWith KlippShell, you can use your device as a TV dashboard (Master) or as a smartphone remote control (Slave). Activate Companion Mode in the settings to comfortably control your TV from your smartphone.\n\n5️⃣ PICTURE-IN-PICTURE (PiP)\nAlthough KlippShell fully supports PiP, some TV manufacturers refuse to offer this feature natively. Don\'t worry: In the settings, you will find an advanced function with a precise guide on how to easily unlock PiP on your TV via ADB command!\n\n6️⃣ TV \"NOW LIVE\" FEATURE\nIf you want to use the \"Now Live\" TV feature, manufacturer restrictions may prevent it from being displayed natively on your TV dashboard. In this case, we recommend using an alternative TV launcher like \"Projectivity Launcher\" on the TV device to fully enjoy this feature.</string>
